==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[mædwe|mǣdwe]]'', inflected form of ''[[mæd|mǣd]]'', from Germanic ''*mǣdwon'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*metwa-'' (''*me-'', ‘mow’).  Compare ''[[mead]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmɛdəʊ/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛdəʊ|-ɛdəʊ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[field]] or [[pasture]]; a piece of land covered or cultivated with grass, usually intended to be mown for hay; an area of low lying vegetation, especially near a river.

